update.description: CVE-2024-6387, also known as RegreSSHion, is a high-severity vulnerability found in OpenSSH servers (sshd) running on glibc-based Linux systems. It is a regression of a previously fixed vulnerability (CVE-2006-5051), which means the issue was reintroduced in newer versions of OpenSSH.
